Dear Hans,

I'll study the Pulay paper and see if we can add this calculation to our
SCF code.  It certainly seems trivial, assuming the density is just the sum
of the alpha and beta components.  The S^(1/2) must be his orthogonalizer,
though we normally use S^(-1/2), but perhaps that doesn't matter.  Simple
diagonalization of the AO-basis density should be a very simple thing.

-TDC

--
Prof. T. Daniel Crawford
crawdad@vt.edu

