>>>> C2h in Fig. 10S should also read as Cs. Thus, the MOs have Cs symmetry=
, but
>>>> alpha and beta orbitals are equivalent so that the structural symmetry=
 is
>>>> higher, C2h and D2h, respectively. Thus, the formulations should be
>>>> correct. However, we will explain this in the text. See also Anita's
>>>> comments attached.
>>>> I am also attaching a paper on oligoacenes where you see the same
>>>> effect, the symmetry broken orbitals (Figure 2) and the higher symmetr=
